documentation_interface_justification:
A Swagger definition and a Javadoc can be generated while spinning up a backend server. But it is not yet provided as part of the documentation for the end-users.

Input for Gradle plugin: https://eclipse.github.io/steady/user/manuals/setup/#gradle
Input for Maven plugin: https://eclipse.github.io/steady/user/manuals/setup/#maven

version_unique_justification:
Semver is used
Releases are tagged on GitHub: https://github.com/eclipse/steady/releases
Java artifacts are deployed on Maven: https://search.maven.org/search?q=com.sap.research.security.vulas
release_notes_justification: https://github.com/eclipse/steady/releases includes descriptions of bug fixes, improvements, features and breaking changes.
report_process_justification: Read https://eclipse.github.io/steady/contributor/#report-bugs, then open an issue at https://github.com/SAP/vulnerability-assessment-tool/issues/new/choose or a StackOverflow question at https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/vulas.
report_responses_justification: All issues are acknowledged and tried to be fixed with major priority
enhancement_responses_justification: All requests are and were answered
build_justification:
Non-trivial build file in repository: https://github.com/eclipse/steady/blob/master/pom.xml
Docs' build process: https://github.com/eclipse/steady/tree/master/docs
Easy docker setup process: https://github.com/eclipse/steady/tree/master/docker and https://eclipse.github.io/steady/admin/
build_common_tools_justification:
Non-trivial build file in repository: https://github.com/eclipse/steady/blob/master/pom.xml
Maven is used to build the Java core components. Docker to build the test containers. Python to build the documentation.
build_floss_tools_justification: Maven and Docker are FLOSS, see pom.xml and .travis.yml for information about other FLOSS tools used during the build.
test_justification: JUnit tests and integration tests are part of every Maven module
test_invocation_justification: JUnit tests and integration tests are invoked with the Maven Surefire and Failsafe plugins (`mvn test`).
test_policy_justification: Tests of new functionalities are informally asked for new tests to be added. Core contributors add tests.
tests_are_added_justification: New features are asked to be tested.
tests_documented_added_justification: The requirements to add tests is documented at https://eclipse.github.io/steady/contributor/#contribution-content-guidelines.
warnings_justification: The Maven compiler plugin has been configured to show compilation and depreciation warnings. Such warnings are reviewed and - where applicable - addressed by the core developers.
warnings_fixed_justification: Warnings are reviewed and addressed by the core developers where applicable.
warnings_strict_justification: The following flags are enabled in the default Maven build: maven.compiler.showWarnings and maven.compiler.showDeprecation
know_secure_design_justification: The core developers work for many years in security research and security testing departments.
crypto_published_justification: Steady makes use of cryptographic hash functions to identify and distinguish application dependencies (e.g., Java archives). Here, it uses standard digest algorithms provided in the java.security package.
crypto_call_justification: Steady itself does not implement any cryptographic functions, algorithms or protocols.
crypto_keylength_justification: The core logic of the application does not encrypt anything on its own.
crypto_working_justification: Steady makes use of SHA1, however, not in the context of a security mechanism (but to identify and differentiate application dependencies, e.g., archives, which are managed by dependency managers and kept in the file system).
crypto_password_storage_justification: No passwords are stored, and no user management is present.
delivery_mitm_justification: Users can protect all client-server communication with HTTPS by creating and installing certificates and configuring the respective endpoints.
static_analysis_justification: Spotbugs is run for every PR.
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: Spotbugs includes a number of security checks: https://spotbugs.readthedocs.io/en/latest/bugDescriptions.html#security-security
static_analysis_often_justification: Spotbugs is run for every PR
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: The project is developed in Java and Python.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: Travis jobs are used to build and test the Java core application, to check code style and analyze the code using Spotbugs, to build the Javadoc and src artifacts (required for deployments on Maven Central), to check if the documentation is buildable and if there are dead links, and - finally - to build and test Docker containers.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
english_justification:
Docs for users: https://sap.github.io/vulnerability-assessment-tool/user/
Docs for admins: https://sap.github.io/vulnerability-assessment-tool/admin/
Docs for reporting: bugs: https://eclipse.github.io/steady/contributor/#report-bugs
hardened_site_justification: Found all required security hardening headers. // X-Content-Type-Options was not set to "nosniff".
installation_common_justification: The software comprises several client and server components. The former are managed by Maven, Gradle or PIP, and the latter are installed/operated using Docker.
implementation_languages: Java, JavaScript, Python, ANTLR, Smarty, TSQL, Go, Shell, Groovy, Dockerfile, Makefile, PLpgSQL
access_continuity_justification: The number of contributors is sufficiently large to backup the disappearance of 2-3 contributors (https://github.com/eclipse/steady/graphs/contributors, https://eclipse.github.io/steady/about/#contributors). Secrets needed for the release process are shared using an internal, protected Web page.
bus_factor_justification: The truck-factor tool computed a bus factor of 1 for https://github.com/eclipse/steady (August 19th 2020).
vulnerability_report_credit_justificatio: No vulnerabilities reported in the last 12 months.
coding_standards_justification: The project follows the Google Java Style Guide (https://google.github.io/styleguide/javaguide.html).
coding_standards_enforced_justification: Compliance is checked for every pull request in a dedicated Travis job.
build_standard_variables_justification: No native binaries are created, only platform-independent Python and Java archives.
installation_standard_variables_justific: For client components, e.g., scan plugins, this is handled by the respective dependency manager (Maven, Gradle or PIP).
external_dependencies_justification: Dependencies are declared via Maven in various pom.xml files, e.g., https://github.com/eclipse/steady/blob/master/pom.xml
updateable_reused_components_justificati: Component updates can be implemented by modifying the pom.xml files.
automated_integration_testing_justificat: A dedicated Travis build job executes all JUnit and integration tests for every PR.
